cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.NI 

This paper deals with distributed fault-tolerant computing, which is a core topic in computer science. The paper introduces asymmetric Byzantine quorum systems, which are a novel concept in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also presents protocols for implementing shared memory and broadcast primitives, which are related to the categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper deals with trust assumptions, which is related to the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with Byzantine faults, which is related to the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
